---
import RealestateLayout from '../../../layouts/RealestateLayout.astro';
import CtaButton from '../../../components/CtaButton.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../../../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<RealestateLayout
  title="North York Real Estate | Neighbourhood Profile | Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent"
  description="North York real estate neighbourhood profile: housing types, price ranges, schools, transit, and market insights from Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent, Trustwell Realty Inc., Brokerage."
  canonicalPath="/neighbourhoods/north-york"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>North York Real Estate: A Neighbourhood Profile</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__subtitle">
        Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent | Trustwell Realty Inc., Brokerage
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="profile">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="profile__content">
        <p class="profile__intro">
          North York is where a significant portion of GTA first-time and move-up buying
          activity occurs. It's geographically central, well-served by the TTC, and offers
          more housing options at more accessible prices than the central Toronto core. Buyers
          priced out of the Annex or Riverdale often find a path to homeownership here without
          leaving the city.
        </p>

        <h2>Character and Feel</h2>
        <p>
          North York is not a single neighbourhood. It's a large district that includes
          Willowdale, Bayview Village, Bathurst Manor, Don Mills, Lawrence Manor, Wilson
          Heights, and others. Each has its own character and price point.
        </p>
        <p>
          Willowdale (centred around Yonge and Sheppard) is the urban core of North York, with
          high-rise condos, restaurants, and a dense retail district. Don Mills is quieter and
          suburban, with more detached homes and proximity to the Shops at Don Mills. Bayview
          Village is upscale, with larger lots and mature trees. Lawrence Manor and Bathurst
          Manor are established communities with strong neighbourhood ties.
        </p>

        <h2>Who Buys in North York</h2>
        <p>
          First-time buyers are active in the Willowdale condo market and in the more accessible
          pockets of Wilson Heights and Lawrence Manor. Move-up buyers seek detached homes in
          Bayview Village and Don Mills. Investors buy condos near Sheppard and Yonge for the
          rental demand from Seneca College's Newnham campus and the surrounding employment base.
        </p>

        <h2>Housing Types and Price Ranges</h2>
        <ul class="price-list">
          <li><strong>Condo apartments in Willowdale and along the Sheppard corridor:</strong> approximately $500K for a one-bedroom to $1.1M for larger two-bedrooms and dens</li>
          <li><strong>Detached homes in Lawrence Manor and Bathurst Manor:</strong> approximately $1.2M to $1.7M</li>
          <li><strong>Detached homes in Bayview Village and Willowdale:</strong> approximately $1.8M to $3M and above</li>
          <li><strong>Freehold townhomes near Yonge-Sheppard and in Don Mills:</strong> approximately $1.1M to $1.6M</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="profile__disclaimer">
          These are general estimates from early 2026. Cory will give you a specific assessment.
        </p>

        <h2>Transit and TTC Access</h2>
        <p>
          North York has strong TTC coverage. Line 1 (Yonge-University) runs the full length of
          the district, with stations at Sheppard, Bessarion, Leslie, Bayview, and Finch. Line 4
          (Sheppard) connects Sheppard-Yonge to Don Mills. TTC bus routes fill the gaps.
        </p>
        <p>
          Residents without a car commute effectively from most parts of North York. The subway
          puts downtown Toronto 20 to 35 minutes away.
        </p>

        <h2>Amenities and Schools</h2>
        <p>
          The North York Civic Centre area includes the Toronto Public Library's North York
          branch, Mel Lastman Square, and retail. Fairview Mall and Yorkdale, just south of the
          district boundary, are the main shopping centres. The Aga Khan Museum and Ismaili
          Centre in Don Mills are notable cultural institutions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Public secondary schools include Earl Haig Secondary School (strong arts program) and
          AY Jackson Secondary School. The Toronto Catholic District School Board serves Catholic
          families in the district.
        </p>

        <h2>Real Estate Perspective</h2>
        <p>
          North York's condo market has softened in 2025 and 2026, in line with the broader
          Toronto condo correction. Active listings are up and sales-to-list ratios have come in.
          For buyers, this creates negotiating room that didn't exist during the 2021-2022 peak.
          For sellers, pricing realistically from the start is the right approach.
        </p>
        <p>
          The detached and freehold townhome market in North York is less affected by the condo
          softness. Demand for family-sized homes near good schools in established neighbourhoods
          has held steady.
        </p>
        <p>
          Which sub-area fits depends on your priorities. Condos near Sheppard-Yonge suit buyers
          who want walkability and transit. Family-sized homes in Don Mills or Bayview Village
          suit buyers willing to trade a longer commute for space.
        </p>

        <div class="profile__cta">
          <CtaButton href="/contact" label="Book a Consultation" variant="primary" />
        </div>

        <p class="profile__compliance">
          Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent. Real estate services provided through Trustwell Realty
          Inc., Brokerage.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <NewsletterSignup heading="Get GTA Market Updates" />
</RealestateLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-hero__subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .profile {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .profile__content {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .profile__intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .profile__content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .profile__content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .price-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .price-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .price-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.5rem;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .profile__disclaimer {
    font-size: 0.8125rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .profile__cta {
    text-align: center;
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .profile__compliance {
    font-size: 0.8125rem !important;
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-style: italic;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
</style>
